This paper is about the analysis of a reinforcement learning algorithm with linear function approximation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the convergence of a stochastic approximation algorithm, which is related to optimization and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves some statistical analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks in reinforcement learning may also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
